<h2 style="color: #d0596f;" class="heading-details">Details</h2>
<p style="color: #1e7e34;text-align:justify;" class="">
    <mark  style="color: #efef8f;background: #6e8197;font-size: 25px">
    Da Nang is a beautiful coastal city located in central Vietnam. With its stunning natural scenery, rich history and culture, and modern amenities, Da Nang has become a popular destination for both domestic and international tourists.
    One of the most famous attractions in Da Nang is My Khe Beach, which has been voted as one of the most beautiful beaches in the world. The long stretch of white sand, crystal-clear water, and fresh sea breeze create a perfect setting for swimming, sunbathing, and relaxing.
    In addition to the beach, there are many other tourist spots in Da Nang, such as the Dragon Bridge, Son Tra Peninsula, Linh Ung Pagoda, Ba Na Hills, Cham Museum, and Da Nang Museum of Fine Arts. Each of these attractions provides a unique experience and insight into the city's history and culture.
    Da Nang also offers a wide range of delicious food, from street food to high-end restaurants, showcasing the unique flavors of Central Vietnam. Some of the must-try dishes include banh xeo (Vietnamese crepe), mi Quang (Quang noodle), and bun cha ca (fish cake noodle soup).
    </mark>
